Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Siderar Advance; YPF Declines

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-27T21:57:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/argentine-stocks-siderar-saic-advances-ypf-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.8 percent to 3,314.71.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  , Argentina’s largest lender by
market value, advanced 1.7 percent to 15.35 pesos. The price of
Argentine sovereign bonds rose, which signals higher value for
banks’ fixed-income holdings.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)  , Argentina’s largest steel producer,
rose 1.2 percent to 30.75 pesos. Argentine economic activity
rose 7.1 percent in April from a year earlier and 0.7 percent
from March, the national statistics institute in  Buenos Aires 
reported on June 24.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , the Argentine unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF,
fell 0.8 percent to 178.50 pesos as oil declined amid concern
that economic expansion in the U.S. is slowing after a report
showed  consumer spending  stagnated last month. Oil for August
delivery dropped 55 cents or 0.6 percent, to $90.61 a barrel on
the  New York Mercantile Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
